Johannesburg - President Cyril Ramaphosa holds an emergency cabinet meeting on Friday to try and resolve a power crisis that has dented growth in Africa's most industrialised economy and endangers its last investment-grade credit rating.
Struggling state utility Eskom implemented the most extensive power cuts in more than a decade earlier this week, disrupting supply to businesses and households. It said it would reduce power for a ninth straight day on Friday.

Eskom is choking under a massive R450 billion debt burden and struggles to meet electricity demand because its creaking coal-fired power stations haven't been maintained properly.
